{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|1Sa|15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","chapter":15,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":1,"text":"Samuel told Saul, “The Lord sent me to anoint you as king over his people Israel. Now, listen to the words of the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":2,"text":"This is what the Lord of Armies says: ‘I witnessed what the Amalekites did to the Israelites when they opposed them along the way as they were coming out of Egypt.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":3,"text":"Now go and attack the Amalekites and completely destroy everything they have. Do not spare them. Kill men and women, infants and nursing babies, oxen and sheep, camels and donkeys.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":4,"text":"Then Saul summoned the troops and counted them at Telaim: two hundred thousand foot soldiers and ten thousand men from Judah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":5,"text":"Saul came to the city of Amalek and set up an ambush in the wadi.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":6,"text":"He warned the Kenites, “Since you showed kindness to all the Israelites when they came out of Egypt, go on and leave! Get away from the Amalekites, or I’ll sweep you away with them.” So the Kenites withdrew from the Amalekites.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":7,"text":"Then Saul struck down the Amalekites from Havilah all the way to Shur, which is next to Egypt.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":8,"text":"He captured King Agag of Amalek alive, but he completely destroyed all the rest of the people with the sword.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":9,"text":"Saul and the troops spared Agag, and the best of the sheep, goats, cattle, and choice animals, as well as the young rams and the best of everything else. They were not willing to destroy them, but they did destroy all the worthless and unwanted things.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":10,"text":"Then the word of the Lord came to Samuel,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":11,"text":"“I regret that I made Saul king, for he has turned away from following me and has not carried out my instructions.” So Samuel became angry and cried out to the Lord all night.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":12,"text":"Early in the morning Samuel got up to confront Saul, but it was reported to Samuel, “Saul went to Carmel where he set up a monument for himself. Then he turned around and went down to Gilgal.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":13,"text":"When Samuel came to him, Saul said, “May the Lord bless you. I have carried out the Lord’s instructions.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":14,"text":"Samuel replied, “Then what is this sound of sheep, goats, and cattle I hear?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":15,"text":"Saul answered, “The troops brought them from the Amalekites and spared the best sheep, goats, and cattle in order to offer a sacrifice to the Lord your God, but the rest we destroyed.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":16,"text":"“Stop!” exclaimed Samuel. “Let me tell you what the Lord said to me last night.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":17,"text":"Samuel continued, “Although you once considered yourself unimportant, haven’t you become the leader of the tribes of Israel? The Lord anointed you king over Israel","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":18,"text":"and then sent you on a mission and said, ‘Go and completely destroy the sinful Amalekites. Fight against them until you have annihilated them.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":19,"text":"So why didn’t you obey the Lord? Why did you rush on the plunder and do what was evil in the Lord’s sight?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":20,"text":"“But I did obey the Lord!” Saul answered. “I went on the mission the Lord gave me: I brought back King Agag of Amalek, and I completely destroyed the Amalekites.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":21,"text":"The troops took sheep, goats, and cattle from the plunder —the best of what was set apart for destruction —to sacrifice to the Lord your God at Gilgal.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":22,"text":"Then Samuel said:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":23,"text":"For rebellion is like the sin of divination,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":24,"text":"Saul answered Samuel, “I have sinned. I have transgressed the Lord’s command and your words. Because I was afraid of the people, I obeyed them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":25,"text":"Now therefore, please forgive my sin and return with me so I can worship the Lord.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":26,"text":"Samuel replied to Saul, “I will not return with you. Because you rejected the word of the Lord, the Lord has rejected you from being king over Israel.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":27,"text":"When Samuel turned to go, Saul grabbed the corner of his robe, and it tore.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":28,"text":"Samuel said to him, “The Lord has torn the kingship of Israel away from you today and has given it to your neighbor who is better than you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":29,"text":"Furthermore, the Eternal One of Israel does not lie or change his mind, for he is not man who changes his mind.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":30,"text":"Saul said, “I have sinned. Please honor me now before the elders of my people and before Israel. Come back with me so I can bow in worship to the Lord your God.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":31,"text":"Then Samuel went back, following Saul, and Saul bowed down to the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":32,"text":"Samuel said, “Bring me King Agag of Amalek.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":33,"text":"Samuel declared:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":34,"text":"Samuel went to Ramah, and Saul went up to his home in Gibeah of Saul.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","bookOrder":8,"chapter":15,"verse":35,"text":"Even to the day of his death, Samuel never saw Saul again. Samuel mourned for Saul, and the Lord regretted he had made Saul king over Israel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Sa","chapter":15,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,7,10,12,14,15,16,17,20,22,23,24,26,30,32,33,34],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Saul Rejected as King"}],"poetryBlocks":[{"beforeVerse":23,"level":1}],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel told Saul, “The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" sent me to anoint you as king over his people Israel. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 9:16","book":"1Sa","chapter":9,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Now, listen to the words of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 9:16","book":"1Sa","chapter":9,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"This is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies says: ‘I witnessed "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"LXX reads I will avenge"},{"kind":"text","text":" what the Amalekites did to the Israelites when they opposed them along the way as they were coming out of Egypt. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 17:8–16","book":"Exo","chapter":17,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 24:20","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 25:17","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":17,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 17:8–16","book":"Exo","chapter":17,"verse":8},{"label":"Nm 24:20","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":20},{"label":"Dt 25:17","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"LXX reads I will avenge"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now go and attack the Amalekites and completely destroy everything they have. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 24:20","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 20:16","book":"Deu","chapter":20,"verse":16,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Do not spare them. Kill men and women, infants and nursing babies, oxen and sheep, camels and donkeys.’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 6:17–21","book":"Jos","chapter":6,"verse":17,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 22:19","book":"1Sa","chapter":22,"verse":19,"letter":"d"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 24:20","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":20},{"label":"Dt 20:16","book":"Deu","chapter":20,"verse":16},{"label":"Jos 6:17–21","book":"Jos","chapter":6,"verse":17},{"label":"1Sm 22:19","book":"1Sa","chapter":22,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Saul summoned the troops and counted them at Telaim: two hundred thousand foot soldiers and ten thousand men from Judah. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Saul came to the city of Amalek and set up an ambush in the wadi. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He warned the Kenites, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 1:16","book":"Jdg","chapter":1,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 4:11","book":"Jdg","chapter":4,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" “Since you showed kindness to all the Israelites when they came out of Egypt, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 18:9–10","book":"Exo","chapter":18,"verse":9,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 10:29","book":"Num","chapter":10,"verse":29,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" go on and leave! Get away from the Amalekites, or I’ll sweep you away with them.” So the Kenites withdrew from the Amalekites."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jdg 1:16","book":"Jdg","chapter":1,"verse":16},{"label":"Jdg 4:11","book":"Jdg","chapter":4,"verse":11},{"label":"Ex 18:9–10","book":"Exo","chapter":18,"verse":9},{"label":"Nm 10:29","book":"Num","chapter":10,"verse":29}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Saul struck down the Amalekites "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 14:48","book":"1Sa","chapter":14,"verse":48,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" from Havilah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 16:7","book":"Gen","chapter":16,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 25:17–18","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":17,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" all the way to Shur, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 15:22","book":"Exo","chapter":15,"verse":22,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 27:8","book":"1Sa","chapter":27,"verse":8,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" which is next to Egypt. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 14:48","book":"1Sa","chapter":14,"verse":48},{"label":"Gn 16:7","book":"Gen","chapter":16,"verse":7},{"label":"Gn 25:17–18","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":17},{"label":"Ex 15:22","book":"Exo","chapter":15,"verse":22},{"label":"1Sm 27:8","book":"1Sa","chapter":27,"verse":8}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He captured King Agag "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 24:7","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Est 3:1","book":"Est","chapter":3,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Amalek alive, but he completely destroyed all the rest of the people with the sword. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 27:8","book":"1Sa","chapter":27,"verse":8,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 30:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":30,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 8:12","book":"2Sa","chapter":8,"verse":12,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 24:7","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":7},{"label":"Est 3:1","book":"Est","chapter":3,"verse":1},{"label":"1Sm 27:8","book":"1Sa","chapter":27,"verse":8},{"label":"1Sm 30:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":30,"verse":1},{"label":"2Sm 8:12","book":"2Sa","chapter":8,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Saul and the troops spared Agag, and the best of the sheep, goats, cattle, and choice animals, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit and the second ones"},{"kind":"text","text":" as well as the young rams and the best of everything else. They were not willing to destroy them, but they did destroy all the worthless and unwanted things."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit and the second ones"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then the word of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" came to Samuel, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“I regret that I made Saul king, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 6:6–7","book":"Gen","chapter":6,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 32:14","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 24:16","book":"2Sa","chapter":24,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" for he has turned away from following me and has not carried out my instructions.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 9:6","book":"1Ki","chapter":9,"verse":6,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" So Samuel became angry and cried out to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" all night. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 32:11–13","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":11,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:12","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":12,"letter":"f"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 6:6–7","book":"Gen","chapter":6,"verse":6},{"label":"Ex 32:14","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":14},{"label":"2Sm 24:16","book":"2Sa","chapter":24,"verse":16},{"label":"1Kg 9:6","book":"1Ki","chapter":9,"verse":6},{"label":"Ex 32:11–13","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":11},{"label":"Lk 6:12","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Early in the morning Samuel got up to confront Saul, but it was reported to Samuel, “Saul went to Carmel "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 15:55","book":"Jos","chapter":15,"verse":55,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 25:2","book":"1Sa","chapter":25,"verse":2,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" where he set up a monument for himself. Then he turned around and went down to Gilgal.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 13:13","book":"1Sa","chapter":13,"verse":13,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 15:55","book":"Jos","chapter":15,"verse":55},{"label":"1Sm 25:2","book":"1Sa","chapter":25,"verse":2},{"label":"1Sm 13:13","book":"1Sa","chapter":13,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Samuel came to him, Saul said, “May the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" bless you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 14:19","book":"Gen","chapter":14,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 2:5","book":"2Sa","chapter":2,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" I have carried out the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s instructions.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 14:19","book":"Gen","chapter":14,"verse":19},{"label":"2Sm 2:5","book":"2Sa","chapter":2,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel replied, “Then what is this sound of sheep, goats, and cattle I hear?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Saul answered, “The troops brought them from the Amalekites and spared the best sheep, goats, and cattle in order to offer a sacrifice to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 3:12–13","book":"Gen","chapter":3,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" but the rest we destroyed.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 32:21–24","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":21,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 3:12–13","book":"Gen","chapter":3,"verse":12},{"label":"Ex 32:21–24","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Stop!” exclaimed Samuel. “Let me tell you what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" said to me last night.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel continued, “Although you once considered yourself unimportant, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 9:21","book":"1Sa","chapter":9,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" haven’t you become the leader of the tribes of Israel? The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" anointed you king over Israel "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 9:21","book":"1Sa","chapter":9,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and then sent you on a mission and said, ‘Go and completely destroy the sinful Amalekites. Fight against them until you have annihilated them.’ "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So why didn’t you obey the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"? Why did you rush on the plunder "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 14:32","book":"1Sa","chapter":14,"verse":32,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and do what was evil in the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s sight?”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 14:32","book":"1Sa","chapter":14,"verse":32}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“But I did obey the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"!” Saul answered. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit answered Samuel"},{"kind":"text","text":" “I went on the mission the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" gave me: I brought back King Agag of Amalek, and I completely destroyed the Amalekites. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit answered Samuel"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The troops took sheep, goats, and cattle from the plunder —the best of what was set apart for destruction —to sacrifice to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God at Gilgal.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 32:22–23","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":22,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 32:22–23","book":"Exo","chapter":32,"verse":22}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Samuel said:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For rebellion is like the sin of divination, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 18:10","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Saul answered Samuel, “I have sinned. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 22:34","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":34,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 12:13","book":"2Sa","chapter":12,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 51:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":51,"verse":3,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" I have transgressed the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s command "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 29:25","book":"Pro","chapter":29,"verse":25,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 51:12–13","book":"Isa","chapter":51,"verse":12,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" and your words. Because I was afraid of the people, I obeyed them. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 22:34","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":34},{"label":"2Sm 12:13","book":"2Sa","chapter":12,"verse":13},{"label":"Ps 51:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":51,"verse":3},{"label":"Pr 29:25","book":"Pro","chapter":29,"verse":25},{"label":"Is 51:12–13","book":"Isa","chapter":51,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now therefore, please forgive my sin "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 10:17","book":"Exo","chapter":10,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and return with me so I can worship the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":".”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 10:17","book":"Exo","chapter":10,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel replied to Saul, “I will not return with you. Because you rejected the word of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 13:14","book":"1Sa","chapter":13,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 16:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" has rejected you from being king over Israel.” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 13:14","book":"1Sa","chapter":13,"verse":14},{"label":"1Sm 16:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Samuel turned to go, Saul grabbed the corner of his robe, and it tore. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel said to him, “The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" has torn the kingship of Israel away from you today "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 28:17","book":"1Sa","chapter":28,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and has given it to your neighbor who is better than you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 11:30","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":30,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 28:17","book":"1Sa","chapter":28,"verse":17},{"label":"1Kg 11:30","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":30}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Furthermore, the Eternal One of Israel "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 29:11","book":"1Ch","chapter":29,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 18:1–2","book":"Psa","chapter":18,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" does not lie or change his mind, for he is not man who changes his mind.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 23:19","book":"Num","chapter":23,"verse":19,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 24:14","book":"Ezk","chapter":24,"verse":14,"letter":"d"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Ch 29:11","book":"1Ch","chapter":29,"verse":11},{"label":"Ps 18:1–2","book":"Psa","chapter":18,"verse":1},{"label":"Nm 23:19","book":"Num","chapter":23,"verse":19},{"label":"Ezk 24:14","book":"Ezk","chapter":24,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:30","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Saul said, “I have sinned. Please honor me "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 12:43","book":"Jhn","chapter":12,"verse":43,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" now before the elders of my people and before Israel. Come back with me so I can bow in worship to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 29:13","book":"Isa","chapter":29,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jn 12:43","book":"Jhn","chapter":12,"verse":43},{"label":"Is 29:13","book":"Isa","chapter":29,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:31","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Samuel went back, following Saul, and Saul bowed down to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:32","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel said, “Bring me King Agag of Amalek.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:33","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel declared:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:34","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel went to Ramah, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 7:17","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and Saul went up to his home in Gibeah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 11:4","book":"1Sa","chapter":11,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Saul. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 7:17","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":17},{"label":"1Sm 11:4","book":"1Sa","chapter":11,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:15:35","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Even to the day of his death, Samuel never saw Saul again. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 19:24","book":"1Sa","chapter":19,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Samuel mourned for Saul, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 16:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" regretted he had made Saul king over Israel."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 19:24","book":"1Sa","chapter":19,"verse":24},{"label":"1Sm 16:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783099289847}